On Monday 15th July a Horse Chestnut tree was planted in North Cadbury school playing field. Mr Barnes, head of the school, gave us the tree. It was planted by Stuart Down and Kieran Woof. They planted it to give shade, it replaced a favourite old tree which we loved to climb. We hope that in many years time Stuart and Kieran will bring their family here to see the tree they planted.
